<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <!--
    NSAppTransportSecurity exception for SAR Tracker desktop.

    Why: Mountain Rescue teams self-host Traccar (the operator's GPS tracker
    server) on a wide variety of HTTP and HTTPS endpoints. Default macOS App
    Transport Security blocks plain HTTP loads from the WKWebView renderer,
    which means the renderer's tracking poller cannot reach a team's Traccar
    instance even when the configuration is correct. Without this entry the
    fetch() calls in src/features/tracking/traccar-client.ts silently fail on
    any non-HTTPS Traccar server, producing the "configured but no devices"
    failure surface from sartracker-web-el9.

    NSAllowsArbitraryLoads is intentionally broad here because each team's
    Traccar server URL is operator-configured and not known at build time.
    A per-domain exception would force every team to use the same upstream
    host and would break the field deployment story. This bundle is internal
    beta only and is never submitted to the App Store, so the App Store
    rejection criterion for arbitrary loads does not apply.

    A separate follow-up bead (`sartracker-web-ats-replacement`) tracks the
    long-term replacement: routing renderer fetch through a Rust reqwest-
    backed Tauri command which bypasses ATS entirely without needing this
    blanket exception.
  -->
  <key>NSAppTransportSecurity</key>
  <dict>
    <key>NSAllowsArbitraryLoads</key>
    <true/>
  </dict>
</dict>
</plist>
